{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.12","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":14951015,"datasetId":9568928,"databundleVersionId":15821229}],"dockerImageVersionId":31286,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Iterated Robust Tabu Search for MAX-SAT\n**Smyth, Hoos & Stützle — Canadian AI 2003**\n\n---\n\n## 1. Le problème : MAX-SAT\n\nOn dispose d'une formule booléenne en **forme normale conjonctive (CNF)** :\n- $n$ variables booléennes $x_1, \\ldots, x_n$\n- $m$ clauses $C_1, \\ldots, C_m$ — chaque clause est une disjonction de littéraux\n\n**Objectif** : trouver une affectation $s \\in \\{0,1\\}^n$ qui maximise le nombre de clauses satisfaites.\n\nDans la version **pondérée**, chaque clause $C_i$ a un poids $w_i > 0$ et on maximise $\\sum_{i \\,:\\, C_i \\text{ satisfaite}} w_i$.\n\n---\n\n## 2. L'approche : IRoTS\n\n**IRoTS = ILS + RoTS**\n\nLe cadre général est ILS (Iterated Local Search). La particularité : le **même algorithme RoTS** est utilisé pour les deux phases.\n\n```\ns  ← solution initiale aléatoire\ns_best ← s\nTANT QUE critère d'arrêt non atteint :\n    s*     ← RoTS(s,  durée_longue)   # intensification → optimum local\n    s_best ← meilleur(s*, s_best)\n    s      ← RoTS(s*, durée_courte)   # perturbation guidée → sortir du bassin\nRETOURNER s_best\n```\n\n### 2.1 RoTS — Robust Tabu Search\n\n- **Voisinage** : flip d'une variable ($x_i : 0 \\leftrightarrow 1$)\n- **Liste taboue** : `flip(i)` interdit pendant `tenure` itérations après usage\n- **Sélection** : meilleur flip non tabou\n- **Critère d'aspiration** : un flip tabou est quand même accepté s'il améliore `s_best`\n\n### 2.2 Double rôle\n\n| Phase | Durée | But |\n|-------|-------|-----|\n| Intensification | longue (`ls_steps`) | atteindre un bon optimum local |\n| Perturbation    | courte (`p_steps`)  | s'échapper intelligemment du bassin d'attraction |\n\nLa perturbation n'est **pas aléatoire** — RoTS guide la sortie, ce qui la rend plus efficace qu'un random restart.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n## 3. Implémentation","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"import random\nimport time\nimport numpy as np\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-17T20:32:52.277321Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-17T20:32:52.277576Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-17T20:32:52.281274Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-17T20:32:52.277556Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-17T20:32:52.280592Z"},"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":2},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 3.1 Instance MAX-SAT","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"class MAXSATInstance:\n    \"\"\"\n    Instance MAX-SAT en format CNF (convention DIMACS).\n    Littéral positif  +k → variable x_k doit être vraie.\n    Littéral négatif  -k → variable x_k doit être fausse.\n    \"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, n_vars, clauses, weights=None):\n        self.n = n_vars\n        self.clauses = clauses\n        self.m = len(clauses)\n        self.weights = weights if weights is not None else [1] * self.m\n        # Précalcul : pour chaque variable i, liste des (clause_idx, signe)\n        # Permet un calcul de delta en O(clauses contenant i) au lieu de O(m)\n        self.var_clauses = [[] for _ in range(n_vars)]\n        for k, clause in enumerate(clauses):\n            for lit in clause:\n                i = abs(lit) - 1\n                self.var_clauses[i].append((k, 1 if lit > 0 else -1))\n\n    def evaluate(self, s):\n        total = 0\n        for k, clause in enumerate(self.clauses):\n            for lit in clause:\n                if (s[abs(lit)-1] == 1) == (lit > 0):\n                    total += self.weights[k]\n                    break\n        return total\n\n    def compute_sat_counts(self, s):\n        \"\"\"sat_count[k] = nombre de littéraux satisfaits dans la clause k.\"\"\"\n        sat = [0] * self.m\n        for k, clause in enumerate(self.clauses):\n            for lit in clause:\n                if (s[abs(lit)-1] == 1) == (lit > 0):\n                    sat[k] += 1\n        return sat\n\n    def delta_flip(self, s, i, sat_count):\n        \"\"\"Gain objectif si flip(i), calculé en O(|var_clauses[i]|).\"\"\"\n        delta = 0\n        new_val = 1 - s[i]\n        for (k, sign) in self.var_clauses[i]:\n            lit_sat_before = (s[i] == 1) == (sign == 1)\n            lit_sat_after  = (new_val == 1) == (sign == 1)\n            if lit_sat_before and not lit_sat_after:\n                if sat_count[k] == 1:   # clause perd son seul littéral satisfait\n                    delta -= self.weights[k]\n            elif not lit_sat_before and lit_sat_after:\n                if sat_count[k] == 0:   # clause était vide, devient satisfaite\n                    delta += self.weights[k]\n        return delta\n\n    def apply_flip(self, s, i, sat_count):\n        \"\"\"Applique flip(i) et met à jour sat_count.\"\"\"\n        new_val = 1 - s[i]\n        for (k, sign) in self.var_clauses[i]:\n            lit_before = (s[i] == 1) == (sign == 1)\n            lit_after  = (new_val == 1) == (sign == 1)\n            if lit_before and not lit_after:\n                sat_count[k] -= 1\n            elif not lit_before and lit_after:\n                sat_count[k] += 1\n        s[i] = new_val","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-17T20:32:56.173545Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-17T20:32:56.173845Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-17T20:32:56.183846Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-17T20:32:56.173822Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-17T20:32:56.183192Z"},"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":3},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 3.2 Générateurs d'instances","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"def random_3sat(n_vars, n_clauses, seed=None):\n    \"\"\"Génère une instance Random-3-SAT non pondérée.\"\"\"\n    if seed is not None: random.seed(seed)\n    clauses = []\n    for _ in range(n_clauses):\n        vars_ = random.sample(range(1, n_vars+1), 3)\n        clause = [v if random.random() > 0.5 else -v for v in vars_]\n        clauses.append(clause)\n    return MAXSATInstance(n_vars, clauses)\n\ndef weighted_3sat(n_vars, n_clauses, w_max=100, seed=None):\n    \"\"\"Génère une instance Random-3-SAT pondérée (haute variance).\"\"\"\n    inst = random_3sat(n_vars, n_clauses, seed)\n    if seed is not None: random.seed(seed + 1)\n    inst.weights = [random.randint(1, w_max) for _ in range(n_clauses)]\n    return inst","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-17T20:33:02.800022Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-17T20:33:02.800298Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-17T20:33:02.806525Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-17T20:33:02.800280Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-17T20:33:02.805591Z"},"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":5},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 3.3 RoTS — Robust Tabu Search","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"def rots(instance, s_init, n_steps, tenure, sat_count_init=None):\n    \"\"\"\n    Robust Tabu Search adapté à MAX-SAT.\n\n    Paramètres\n    ----------\n    n_steps  : nombre d'itérations (long = intensification, court = perturbation)\n    tenure   : durée taboue d'un flip\n\n    Retourne s_best, f_best, sat_count_best\n    \"\"\"\n    n = instance.n\n    s = list(s_init)\n    sat_count = list(sat_count_init) if sat_count_init else instance.compute_sat_counts(s)\n    f = sum(instance.weights[k] for k in range(instance.m) if sat_count[k] > 0)\n\n    s_best, f_best, sat_best = list(s), f, list(sat_count)\n    tabu_until = [0] * n\n\n    for step in range(1, n_steps + 1):\n        best_delta, best_i = None, -1\n\n        for i in range(n):\n            delta = instance.delta_flip(s, i, sat_count)\n            is_tabu = tabu_until[i] >= step\n            # Critère d'aspiration : on accepte un mouvement tabou s'il améliore s_best\n            if is_tabu and (f + delta <= f_best):\n                continue\n            if best_delta is None or delta > best_delta:\n                best_delta, best_i = delta, i\n\n        if best_i == -1:\n            break\n\n        instance.apply_flip(s, best_i, sat_count)\n        f += best_delta\n        tabu_until[best_i] = step + tenure\n\n        if f > f_best:\n            f_best = f\n            s_best = list(s)\n            sat_best = list(sat_count)\n\n    return s_best, f_best, sat_best","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-17T20:33:06.891580Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-17T20:33:06.891874Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-17T20:33:06.898059Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-17T20:33:06.891855Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-17T20:33:06.897293Z"},"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":6},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 3.4 IRoTS — Iterated Robust Tabu Search","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"def irots(instance, ls_steps=300, p_steps=60, tenure=5, max_iter=100, seed=None):\n    \"\"\"\n    Iterated Robust Tabu Search.\n\n    ls_steps : itérations RoTS en phase d'intensification\n    p_steps  : itérations RoTS en phase de perturbation\n    tenure   : durée taboue\n    max_iter : nombre d'itérations ILS\n    \"\"\"\n    if seed is not None: random.seed(seed)\n\n    s = [random.randint(0, 1) for _ in range(instance.n)]\n    sat_count = instance.compute_sat_counts(s)\n    f = sum(instance.weights[k] for k in range(instance.m) if sat_count[k] > 0)\n\n    s_best, f_best = list(s), f\n    history = [f_best]\n\n    for _ in range(max_iter):\n        # Phase 1 : intensification (longue)\n        s_ls, f_ls, sat_ls = rots(instance, s, ls_steps, tenure, sat_count)\n        if f_ls > f_best:\n            f_best, s_best = f_ls, list(s_ls)\n        history.append(f_best)\n\n        # Phase 2 : perturbation guidée (courte) — pas de random restart\n        s, _, sat_count = rots(instance, s_ls, p_steps, tenure, sat_ls)\n\n    return s_best, f_best, history","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-17T20:33:11.416446Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-17T20:33:11.416716Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-17T20:33:11.422176Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-17T20:33:11.416697Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-17T20:33:11.421593Z"},"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":7},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 3.5 Baselines de comparaison","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"def hill_climbing(instance, seed=None):\n    \"\"\"Hill Climbing best-improvement avec voisinage flip.\"\"\"\n    if seed is not None: random.seed(seed)\n    s = [random.randint(0, 1) for _ in range(instance.n)]\n    sat_count = instance.compute_sat_counts(s)\n    f = sum(instance.weights[k] for k in range(instance.m) if sat_count[k] > 0)\n    improved = True\n    while improved:\n        improved = False\n        best_delta, best_i = 0, -1\n        for i in range(instance.n):\n            d = instance.delta_flip(s, i, sat_count)\n            if d > best_delta:\n                best_delta, best_i = d, i\n        if best_i != -1:\n            instance.apply_flip(s, best_i, sat_count)\n            f += best_delta\n            improved = True\n    return f\n\ndef simulated_annealing(instance, T0=5.0, alpha=0.997, max_iter=30000, seed=None):\n    \"\"\"Recuit simulé avec voisinage flip.\"\"\"\n    if seed is not None: random.seed(seed)\n    s = [random.randint(0, 1) for _ in range(instance.n)]\n    sat_count = instance.compute_sat_counts(s)\n    f = sum(instance.weights[k] for k in range(instance.m) if sat_count[k] > 0)\n    f_best = f\n    T = T0\n    for _ in range(max_iter):\n        i = random.randint(0, instance.n - 1)\n        delta = instance.delta_flip(s, i, sat_count)\n        if delta > 0 or random.random() < np.exp(delta / T):\n            instance.apply_flip(s, i, sat_count)\n            f += delta\n            if f > f_best: f_best = f\n        T *= alpha\n    return f_best","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-17T20:33:17.280603Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-17T20:33:17.280917Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-17T20:33:17.288334Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-17T20:33:17.280896Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-17T20:33:17.287720Z"},"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":9},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n## 4. Tests\n\n### 4.1 Exécution de base","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"inst = random_3sat(n_vars=50, n_clauses=215, seed=42)   # ratio 4.3 ≈ seuil de phase\nprint(f\"Instance : {inst.n} variables, {inst.m} clauses\")\n\nt0 = time.time()\ns_best, f_best, history = irots(inst, seed=0)\nelapsed = time.time() - t0\n\nprint(f\"Meilleure solution : {f_best} / {inst.m} clauses satisfaites\")\nprint(f\"Taux de satisfaction : {f_best / inst.m * 100:.1f}%\")\nprint(f\"Temps d'exécution : {elapsed:.2f}s\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-17T20:33:21.586897Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-17T20:33:21.587307Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-17T20:33:23.917589Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-17T20:33:21.587287Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-17T20:33:23.916914Z"},"trusted":true},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Instance : 50 variables, 215 clauses\nMeilleure solution : 214 / 215 clauses satisfaites\nTaux de satisfaction : 99.5%\nTemps d'exécution : 2.33s\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":10},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 4.2 Courbe de convergence","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))\nplt.plot(history, color='#378ADD', linewidth=1.5, label='IRoTS s_best')\nplt.axhline(inst.m, color='#888780', linestyle='--', linewidth=0.9, label=f'Optimum = {inst.m}')\nplt.xlabel(\"Itération ILS\")\nplt.ylabel(\"Clauses satisfaites\")\nplt.title(\"Convergence IRoTS — Random-3-SAT (n=50, m=215)\")\nplt.legend()\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-17T20:33:28.468597Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-17T20:33:28.468895Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-17T20:33:28.685877Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-17T20:33:28.468876Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-17T20:33:28.685052Z"},"trusted":true},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":11},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 4.3 Comparaison HC / SA / IRoTS","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"n_runs = 10\nresults = {'Hill Climbing': [], 'Recuit simulé': [], 'IRoTS': []}\n\nfor run in range(n_runs):\n    inst_r = random_3sat(50, 215, seed=run * 77)\n    results['Hill Climbing'].append(hill_climbing(inst_r, seed=run))\n    results['Recuit simulé'].append(simulated_annealing(inst_r, seed=run))\n    _, f, _ = irots(inst_r, seed=run)\n    results['IRoTS'].append(f)\n\nprint(f\"{'Méthode':<16} {'Moy':>8} {'Écart-type':>12} {'Min':>6} {'Max':>6}\")\nprint(\"-\" * 50)\nfor name, vals in results.items():\n    print(f\"{name:<16} {np.mean(vals):>8.1f} {np.std(vals):>12.2f} {min(vals):>6} {max(vals):>6}\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-17T20:33:33.573427Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-17T20:33:33.573698Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-17T20:33:58.023136Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-17T20:33:33.573677Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-17T20:33:58.022517Z"},"trusted":true},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Méthode               Moy   Écart-type    Min    Max\n--------------------------------------------------\nHill Climbing       209.8         1.78    207    213\nRecuit simulé       214.3         0.90    213    215\nIRoTS               213.8         1.17    211    215\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":12},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 4.4 Visualisation de la comparaison","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 4))\nmethods = list(results.keys())\nmeans = [np.mean(results[m]) for m in methods]\nstds  = [np.std(results[m])  for m in methods]\ncolors = ['#888780', '#1D9E75', '#D85A30']\n\nbars = ax.bar(methods, means, yerr=stds, capsize=5, color=colors, width=0.5, alpha=0.85)\nax.set_ylabel(\"Clauses satisfaites (moyenne sur 10 runs)\")\nax.set_title(\"Comparaison — Random-3-SAT (n=50, m=215)\")\nax.set_ylim(200, 216)\nax.axhline(215, color='gray', linestyle='--', linewidth=0.8, label='max = 215')\nax.legend()\nfor bar, mean in zip(bars, means):\n    ax.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2, bar.get_height() + 0.2,\n            f'{mean:.1f}', ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10)\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-17T20:34:07.259736Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-17T20:34:07.260007Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-17T20:34:07.402231Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-17T20:34:07.259985Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-17T20:34:07.401492Z"},"trusted":true},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 700x400 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":13},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 4.5 MAX-SAT pondéré (haute variance)","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# L'article montre que IRoTS est particulièrement fort sur les instances pondérées à haute variance\nn_runs = 10\nw_results = {'Hill Climbing': [], 'Recuit simulé': [], 'IRoTS': []}\n\nfor run in range(n_runs):\n    inst_w = weighted_3sat(50, 215, w_max=100, seed=run * 77)\n    w_results['Hill Climbing'].append(hill_climbing(inst_w, seed=run))\n    w_results['Recuit simulé'].append(simulated_annealing(inst_w, seed=run))\n    _, f, _ = irots(inst_w, seed=run)